Module kivakit.core
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.language.module

Class PackageReference

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.path.Path<String>
com.telenav.kivakit.core.path.StringPath
com.telenav.kivakit.core.language.module.PackageReference
All Implemented Interfaces:
Sized, DoubleQuantizable, Quantizable, Stringable, StringSource, Comparable<Path<String>>, Iterable<String>
public final class PackageReference extends StringPath
Represents the path to a Java package. The PackagePath object in kivakit-resource differs from this class.

This class contains numerous methods which down-cast the return value of the superclass to make use easier for clients. Methods that are unique to this class mainly have to do with resources and modules:

  • moduleResources(Listener) - A list of ModuleResources in the package with this path
  • moduleResource(Listener, String) - Any ModuleResource at the given relative path
  • moduleResourceStream(String) - A stream for the resource at the given path relative to this package
  • contains(ModuleResource) - True if this package contains the given resource
  • containsNested(ModuleResource) - True if this package contains the given resource at any depth
  • nestedModuleResources(Listener) - A list of nested module resources in and under this package
  • nestedModuleResources(Listener, Matcher) - A list of nested module resources in and under this package that match the given matcher
  • subPackages(Listener) - The set of all package paths under this one
  • #

Parsing

  • isPackageReference(String) - True if the given string can be parsed as a package path
  • parsePackageReference(Listener listener, String) - The specified package path, separated by either '/' or '.'
  • parsePackageReference(Listener listener, Class, String) - The specified package path, relative to the given class and separated by either '/' or '.'

Factories

  • packageReference(StringPath) - The specified package path
  • packageReference(Class) - The package where the given class resides
  • packageReference(Class, StringPath) - The specified path relative to the given class

Examples

 PackageReference.of(MyClass.class)
 PackageReference.parsePackageReference(MyClass.class, "resources/images")
 PackageReference.parsePackageReference(MyClass.class, "resources.images")
 PackageReference.parsePackageReference(getClass(), "resources/images")
 PackageReference.parsePackageReference("com.telenav.kivakit/core")
 PackageReference.parsePackageReference("com.telenav.kivakit.core")
